DemultiplexTwoOutputReal

This component is used to distribute 32-bit floating point data [In], to an output corresponding to the input event received. For example if the input event [In]s1 is triggered, then the input data [In] will be presented to output [Out]o1 and fire the associated event [Out]1. Note that the data persists at the outputs.

Ports

  • [In] :

    Data input, value of the data to be distributed.

  • [Out] o1:

    Data output 1.

  • [Out] o2:

    Data output 2.

  • [In] s1:

    Event input 1, triggers the corresponding output event and presents data to output [Out]o1.

  • [In] s2:

    Event input 2, triggers the corresponding output event and presents data to output [Out]o2.

  • [Out] :

    Event output 1.

  • [Out] :

    Event output 2.

Parameters

None.

State Machine

Stateless.

Profiles

All.

Toolbox

Core.

Version

v2.1.
